commit_message: WORKFLOWS: Add some github workflows
Make distcheck work (again?)
Fix some multiple definitions of the same variables
More header file inclusion fixes
Fix wrong assignment of allocated memory and include extreme_fit.h
Make loop energy evaluation functions static
Use memcpy instead of strncpy
Make automake happy
Adding example alignments
Merge branch 'master' of git@github.com:wash/rnacode
Adding documentation and touch-ups for paper revision.
Remove weight.[ch] from Makefile. Fixes OSX compile error.
Fix documentation.
Updating version information.
Update documentation and version information
Merge branch 'gh-pages' of git@github.com:wash/rnacode
Updated documentation in README file.

Most of the color coding finished. Has still
some rough ends and needs more testing.
Started postscript coloring again.

Fixed subtle bug in algorithm to get HSS. Now HSS are extended
as far as possible on both ends also with neutral sites of score 0.
Add BLOSUM90 to see if this makes any difference at all.
New options "--best-region" and "--best-only"
Added Peter's sequence weighting code (not active yet).

Fixed memory leak and added explicit error handling when
EVD fit fails.
Fix a major bug causing bad and frequent segfaults.
Some documentation for README file.
Implement --best-only feature; handle Ns; bump version number to 0.2beta;

Implemented 'stop-early' feature. This avoids calculating the exact
p-value if its verly likely to be above the specified cutoff.
Writing some documentation.
github generated gh-pages branch

Improved efficiency of calculation of the background model which
is apparently the major bottleneck for short alignments.
Cleaning and preparing for distribution.
Significant speedup (2-3x), crash fixes and cleaning up.

Removed unneccessary function calls from inner loop. Is now 30% faster
but still slower than expected.
Explicit penalizing stop codons.

Statistics should be correct again now. Unfortunately it is even
slower now.
Backtracking and testing code.
Needed to fix all memory leaks before we can go on with testing on real alignments.

Removed unnecessary function call in inner loop which made this cubic;
Scan both forward and reverse complement.
Rewritten most of the code support the new gap-model.
More work on postscript output.

Changed algorithm that not average of every sequence against every other
sequence is used, but only the comparison between the first which each
other. Benchmarks shows that this gives exactly the same results but
is much faster (because it is linear with species number not quadratic)
Removed TODO from Makefile.am
Cleaned up repository a bit before starting again programming
Started with postscript functions and did some more stuff.
Implemented printing of false-positives/false-negatives for debugging
Finalized new matrix version of getHSS, behaves as the previous version
Implemented alternative version of getHSS using a full matrix.
Initial commit
